sql:
SELECT c.customer_id, c.customer_first_name, c.customer_last_name
FROM Customers c
JOIN Orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
JOIN Order_Items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id
GROUP BY c.customer_id, c.customer_first_name, c.customer_last_name
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT o.order_id) > 2 AND COUNT(oi.order_item_id) >= 3;
question: List the id, first name and last name of the customers who both have placed more than 2 orders and have bought at least 3 items.
